SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 933
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate James Webb upon
winning first place in the National Geographic
Bee at Newport Grammar School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should pay tribute to those students who, through their
natural talents and unflagging commitment to academic excellence, have distinguished
themselves in the classroom and their community; and
WHEREAS, James Webb is one such exceptional student, who won first place in the
National Geographic Bee at Newport Grammar School on February 12, 2026; and
WHEREAS, the National Geographic Bee is a geography competition designed to
inspire and reward students' curiosity about the world; and
WHEREAS, a seventh-grade student at Newport Grammar School, where he is highly
regarded by his peers, James Webb has achieved academic success; and
WHEREAS, James Webb's achievement is a tremendous source of pride for his family,
his school, and his community; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Webb's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of our respect,
admiration, and commendation; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate James Webb upon
winning first place in the National Geographic Bee at Newport Grammar School and extend to
him our best wishes for every continued success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
